						               													<description>Mirianth, a kingdom in constant war against terrible monsters and with nations separated by personal interests. Only those who have prepared for war will survive the coming winter.&amp;#10;Be among them!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Mirianth Wars, players are creating their factions trying to earn the loyalty of warriors, build the best dwellings, find the most valuable treasures, and commit to engage in memorable battles against monsters, all through rounds of negotiation with their opponents for the cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;However, when player strategies conflict, diplomacy will be the last resort before luck comes into play. If the players do not come to an agreement, they will face the plague deck, and the outcome will only depend on luck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After everyone has created their faction, they will go through the tests that will define how good their strategy was.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;First, players need to check that all their heroes can be accommodated in residences, from simple huts to sumptuous castles, otherwise they will scatter and leave the player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From the heroes who were accommodated and did not perish to the plague, the battle will begin against the monsters, which if not defeated, will destroy houses, steal treasures or kill the heroes. After the battle, you will once again need to accommodate your heroes in order for them to recover.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Finally, from the surviving heroes, saved treasures, and defeated monsters, the player's points will be counted.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mirianth Wars presents a game of diplomacy and strategy based on the balance between ambition and luck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
